Author: ishaanharry#7544
Content: for any given programmer x in the set of all programmers X, x said "it works"

Author: ishaanharry#7544
Content:
let x be a programmer in the set of all programmers X.
suppose for a contradiction that x did not say "it works".
this implies that x has not made a working program.
if x has not made a working program, then x is not a programmer.
but this contradicts the assertion that x is in the set of all programmers X.
therefore by contradiction, x must have said "it works".
